helpdesk-ticket.subject: Library Color Printer Out of Order?
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello!
I have received many complaints from students that the color printer is currently out of order. The main problems are
1. When printing, instead of printing the student's work, it will print the printer's Start Up pages
2. The printer will often not print and will beep to indicate a student has scanned their ID, but otherwise make no change.
I am unsure if the error is with the printer or the user, as sometimes I have no problems printing in color and other times I find it impossible.
Thank you,
Rachael Ferguson

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Paul Churchill,
Blackboard has a fairly extensive set of video tutorials for instructors and students. I would say that would be the best place to start. For instructors, there is also a "Best Practices Using Blackboard" course in MSOE's Blackboard to which all instructors have access.
Instructor Blackboard Video Tutorials: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLontYaReEU1tzu1T5gfiX-JQA5nBc3isN
Student Blackboard Video Tutorials: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLontYaReEU1seUE3ACG3sEc3zR7Br7URU
I hope this helps.
Sincerely,
Andrew M. Holmes, M.Ed Instructional Technology Technician Office: CC307 email: holmes@msoe.edu phone: x6765 Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/6940

Good news. First, sorry for the delay in responding. We had the resolution yesterday by about 1:00 p.m.
Michael Cordes, one of our student workers, did reinstall the cartridges. At the same time, he ran the setting to clean the print heads, and to recalibrate them. His observation was that the print heads were the real issue.

Please let me know if I should close the ticket.
Vivian

We are hoping you can help provide computer access for a class of visiting St. Joan Antida who will be coming to the library on Wednesday, 4/13 at 11:30am to receive library/RCAS instruction as requested by the VP of Academics, Steve Bialek. The teacher in charge of the class, Susan Kosiboski, has just asked if her students would be able to obtain temporary logins for the student-use laptops in the library or be able to use MSOE IT-provided laptops for this project.
Though not stated explicitly, I am sure there is a hope that our partnering with SJA will result in some of their students eventually attending MSOE. Any cooperation you can provide would be most appreciated. Please let us know how you are able to help us at your earliest opportunity.
Thank you very much!
Sarah Rowell, MLIS Librarian I MSOE Walter Schroeder Library 414-277-7389 rowell@msoe.edu<mailto:rowell@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-ticket.description: I'm currently not enrolled for this Spring quarter due to academic suspension and have as such received notice that my account will be disabled on April 27th, since I intend to return in the Fall after the 2 quarter suspension is it possible to delay the disablement of my account until September? That way I can still maintain contact with the Registrars office, Financial Aid office, and a professor about an Incomplete grade from the Winter Quarter for simpler resolution. Should I for some reason not re-enroll for the Fall quarter then the account could safely be disabled in September. In the case that is not possible what steps would I have to take come July/August to get my account re-enabled for the purposes of contacting the Registrar and registering?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi buddenhagenj, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/7003
Unfortunately we can't keep your account enabled beyond the 27th of April for security reasons. The status of your account is directly linked to your student status and a non-enrolled student does have access to their account until such time that they are enrolled. The process for returning to MSOE in the fall quarter would have to involve contacting the Registrars office and signing up for classes ether in person over the phone. Once you are signed up for classes you will again have access to your account.
Note(your MSOE email box will continue to receive emails while the account is disabled)
Please reply to this ticket if you have any further questions.

helpdesk-note.body: I replaced a VGA cable today on the spot and so the security clamp needs to be taken off of the old cable and put onto the new one. I had noted an issue while doing this though, when I secured the VGA to the connection on the wall, it did not send the connection through, but when I loosed it and jiggled it a bit, it worked again. This issue is not caused by a bad cable since I have witnessed it with three different cables throughout the quarter, and the issue is not limited to one computer because I have seen it while using multiple computers. If we have a spare module on hand, I will look at what it takes to replace it.

helpdesk-note.body: I went over to take a look. When I installed the latest touchpad driver and restarted the computer, the keyboard stopped responding. All hardware worked in the BIOS. It appears as though a recent WIndows update corrupted files. I attempted to perform a system restore and system file checker from a recovery disc; no success. The hard drive in question was a personal SSD, cloned from the original HDD a week ago. Dr. Khalil's son came in, and we devised a plan to copy recent files from the SSD to the HDD, perform the Windows updates to the HDD, and then, if successful, reclone the HDD to the SSD.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I went over to take a look. When I installed the latest touchpad driver and restarted the computer, the keyboard stopped responding. All hardware worked in the BIOS. It appears as though a recent WIndows update corrupted files. I attempted to perform a system restore and system file checker from a recovery disc; no success. The hard drive in question was a personal SSD, cloned from the original HDD a week ago. Dr. Khalil's son came in, and we devised a plan to copy recent files from the SSD to the HDD, perform the Windows updates to the HDD, and then, if successful, reclone the HDD to the SSD.

helpdesk-note.body: Dr. Khalil was able, with the help of his son, to resolve his issue.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: internet
helpdesk-ticket.description: Ethernet Plugin 09-C (In appt 1209) has been up and down with connectivity since February. Assumed at first, just a problem with router or computer, but now I have discovered it is something wrong with the outlet itself or the connections to it. The error that is continuously displaying is an issue with identifying the DNS address. Assuming this was a computer error, I had many friends (SE's) look at my machine and nothing was wrong. When attempting to plug an Ethernet cable straight from the wall to the computer the same message was displayed. This has been the error for multiple computers directly hooked into the outlet.

Hi smithdc,
While in the closet earlier this week, we found that the two ports in the room were looped to each other. This would likely cause the problems you saw. Make sure you are not plugging two wall cables into the same switch or router. To correct the issue, we had to disable the second port in the room at the network closet.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: July 14, 2016
helpdesk-ticket.description:
We have an event on Thursday, July 14th at the Towers, 4th Floor. The event is from 10:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.
We will need to have the session video-taped. We will need two cameras and someone to set up and check on both during the day. The event is from 10:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. RSOB does have one video camera that can be used if you need it. Tripods will also be needed for both cameras. We might have one or two that work for this purpose if IT doesn’t have any. We had two cameras, but I’ve been told that the other one is in IT somewhere, as it was used for Instructional Design.
Can you please add this event to your calendar so that someone can help video this event?
Kim Benson Administrative Assistant Rader School of Business Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 N. Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 (414) 277-7279 benson@msoe.edu<mailto:benson@msoe.edu>
